abstract: There are a lot of lawyers in New York, but few like Jim Walden, who has managed to be a part of some of the biggest political dramas in recent years.
snippet: There are a lot of lawyers in New York, but few like Jim Walden, who has managed to be a part of some of the biggest political dramas in recent years.
lead_paragraph: Two months into his first term as mayor, Bill de Blasio offered resounding praise for the lawyer he worked with during his campaign to oppose the closing of a cherished Brooklyn hospital.

abstract: Hospitals lure diabetes patients with self-management classes, but the education can come with a high price tag.
snippet: Hospitals lure diabetes patients with self-management classes, but the education can come with a high price tag.
lead_paragraph: When a routine physical revealed mildly elevated blood sugar levels, Michael Phillips’s doctor referred him to a diabetes educator. The educator strongly encouraged him to to sign up for a diabetes self-management class.

abstract: The City Council takes up residential parking permits, again. A policy that is prevalent around the country has never gotten far in New York City.
snippet: The City Council takes up residential parking permits, again. A policy that is prevalent around the country has never gotten far in New York City.
lead_paragraph: One after another, the cars with out-of-state license plates roll off the George Washington Bridge into Pedro Richiez’s neighborhood in northern Manhattan. They circle the blocks. They nab parking spots as soon as they open up.
